                            <comment id="14497887" author="apachespark" created="Thu, 16 Apr 2015 10:42:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;viirya&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/5541&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/5541&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14498185" author="rxin" created="Thu, 16 Apr 2015 15:37:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Should we throw an exception if the name is identical, or just replace it? For example, what happens if the user does&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;df.select(df(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;*&quot;&lt;/span&gt;), lit(1).as(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;col&quot;&lt;/span&gt;))
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If df already contains a column named &quot;col&quot;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14498329" author="josephkb" created="Thu, 16 Apr 2015 17:17:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rxin&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rxin&quot;&gt;rxin&lt;/a&gt; Your select statement does highlight how the correct behavior is ambiguous.  What is the best way to replace 1 column while leaving all others the same?  That seems like a useful operation.  (Right now, I can only think of getting all of the column names, removing the one being replaced, and using that list in a select statement.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14498725" author="rxin" created="Thu, 16 Apr 2015 21:03:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=marmbrus&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;marmbrus&quot;&gt;marmbrus&lt;/a&gt; to chime in.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think about it more, and withName should probably overwrite an existing column (or maybe with an argument to control the behavior?). However, we might want a broader discussion about column names also.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14498734" author="rakeshchalasani" created="Thu, 16 Apr 2015 21:09:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Join over to two data frames also leads to a similar issue, if the two frames have same named columns.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I can create separate JIRA issue for this, but the resolution should follow a similar behavior I believe.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14498736" author="josephkb" created="Thu, 16 Apr 2015 21:10:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Btw, when I say &quot;that seems like a useful operation,&quot; I really mean that I wanted to do that for MLlib.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14504030" author="marmbrus" created="Tue, 21 Apr 2015 00:33:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 to &lt;tt&gt;withColumn&lt;/tt&gt; overwriting existing columns.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14504084" author="josephkb" created="Tue, 21 Apr 2015 01:02:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just to clarify, does that mean &lt;tt&gt;withColumn&lt;/tt&gt; does &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; replace columns, but &lt;tt&gt;withName&lt;/tt&gt; does?  (I&apos;m not sure what &lt;tt&gt;withName&lt;/tt&gt; is.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14504092" author="marmbrus" created="Tue, 21 Apr 2015 01:07:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, updated.  I meant &lt;tt&gt;withColumn&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14504149" author="marmbrus" created="Tue, 21 Apr 2015 01:54:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Issue resolved by pull request 5541&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/5541&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/5541&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14700239" author="calstad" created="Mon, 17 Aug 2015 21:10:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This still seems to be an issue in the pyspark implementation of &lt;tt&gt;withColumn&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14700418" author="marmbrus" created="Mon, 17 Aug 2015 23:20:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Filed &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-10073&quot; title=&quot;Python withColumn for existing column name not consistent with scala&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-10073&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-10073&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for python.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16064095" author="yichuan" created="Tue, 27 Jun 2017 01:43:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;withColumn have this strange behavior with join, it replaces both columns from the left and right side of the join, and replace them with the new column (Spark 2.0.2)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;val left = Seq((1, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;one&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;p1&quot;&lt;/span&gt;), (2, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;two&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;b&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;)).toDF(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;id&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;name&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;note&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;note2&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
val right = Seq((1, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;c&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, 11, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;n1&quot;&lt;/span&gt;), (2,  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;, 22, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;n2&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)).toDF(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;id&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,  &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;note&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;seq&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;note2&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
val j = left.join(right, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;id&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
j.show()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;+---+----+----+-----+----+---+-----+
| id|name|note|note2|note|seq|note2|
+---+----+----+-----+----+---+-----+
|  1| one|&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;|   p1|   c| 11|   n1|
|  2| two|   b| &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;|&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;| 22|   n2|
+---+----+----+-----+----+---+-----+
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;val k = j.withColumn(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;note&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, coalesce(left(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;note&quot;&lt;/span&gt;), right(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;note&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)))
k.show()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;+---+----+----+-----+----+---+-----+
| id|name|note|note2|note|seq|note2|
+---+----+----+-----+----+---+-----+
|  1| one|   c|   p1|   c| 11|   n1|
|  2| two|   b| &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;|   b| 22|   n2|
+---+----+----+-----+----+---+-----+
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;val l = k.drop(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;note&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
l.show()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
